subSubSection.paragraph:
Coloration
(Fig. 
5
)

: Cranium, mesosoma and metasoma black; eyes brown to black; ocelli brown; scape and basal pedicel yellow; flagellum dark brown to black; fore and mid coxa along with femur and tibia brown with brownish joints; syntergum brown (Fig. 
5A
); pterostigma and costal vein brown; radial vein brown (Fig. 
5F
); body pubescence white; marginal fringes of wings brown.

Wings
(Fig. 
5F
)

: Total wing length 1.5 mm. Hyaline. Pterostigma (Length/width = 220/110 
μm
) elliptical, 2.0
x
longer than wide; distal edge of pterostigma truncated; Radius (270 
μm
), curved a little in the middle and slightly logger (1.2
x
) than pterostigma; forewing densely pubescent and marginal fringes numerous; hindwing without venation. Dark area on fore wing absent.

Male genitalia
(Fig. 
6
)

: Genitalia with short cupula. Harpe longer than gonostipes in lateral view; simple and not bilobed. Distal margin of harpe in lateral view blunt. Lateral setae of harpe present, but sparse (Fig. 
6B
). Gonostipes longer than wide, fused dorsally; apical margin (part of gonostipes) cleft medially (Fig. 
6A
). Median notch of distodorsal margin of gonostipes oval. Distal parossiculal projection rounded.
